OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,436,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1782238703
OL,3,CNew Welsh Government sets out #249m
OL,4,Cspending plans
OL,6,F"This new Government will ensure that
OL,7,Fevery pound delivers better outcomes `
OL,8,Fbetter childcare, better healthcare
OL,9,Fand better public services for the
OL,10,Fpeople of Wales."
OL,12,FThe Federation of Small Businesses
OL,13,F(FSB) Wales says it welcomes the
OL,14,Fsupplementary budget, but that action
OL,15,Fmust come in the Autumn.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,436,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1782238703
OL,3,CNew Welsh Government sets out #249m
OL,4,Cspending plans
OL,6,FJoshua Miles, Head of FSB Wales, said:
OL,7,F"This supplementary budget keeps
OL,8,Fthings ticking over, but the next
OL,9,Fbudget must go further - delivering
OL,10,Fthe bold measures needed to unlock the
OL,11,Ffull potential of Wales's small
OL,12,Fbusiness community.
OL,14,F"Our members will now be looking ahead
OL,15,Fto the Autumn budget as the key moment
OL,16,Ffor action. That must be the point
OL,17,Fwhere we see meaningful progress on
OL,18,Fthe big-ticket issues holding back
OL,19,Fgrowth in Wales."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,436,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1782238703
OL,3,CNew Welsh Government sets out #249m
OL,4,Cspending plans
OL,6,FHe added that reforming business rates
OL,7,F"remains absolutely critical to easing
OL,8,Fpressures on small firms" and that
OL,9,F"sustained investment" is needed in
OL,10,Ftransport infrastructure as well as a
OL,11,Flong-term commitment to funding the
OL,12,Fnew National Development Agency.
OL,14,FIn response, Sam Rowlands MS, finance
OL,15,Fspokesperson for the Welsh
OL,16,FConservatives said: "We needed a
OL,17,Fbudget to support enterprise, help
OL,18,Fsmall businesses and attract
OL,19,Finvestment into Wales.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,436,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1782238703
OL,3,CNew Welsh Government sets out #249m
OL,4,Cspending plans
OL,6,F"Plaid Cymru have not set aside a
OL,7,Fpenny for hardworking small business
OL,8,Fowners in Wales who face higher
OL,9,Fbusiness rates than in England and
OL,10,Ffarmers too seem to have been ignored.
OL,12,F"This budget offers more of the same
OL,13,Ftired approach that we saw under
OL,14,FLabour. What we need is a budget that
OL,15,Fcuts taxes and gets the Welsh economy
OL,16,Fmoving."
OL,18,FThe remaining four parties in the
OL,19,FSenedd have been approached for
OL,20,Fcomment.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/8
